The paper uses data from a social media website to analyze the geographic flow of music, which involves elements of social networks, data mining, and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses statistical methods to analyze the data, which could fall under cs.SD (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper explores the relationship between music preferences and geographic location, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
